clude Kurt Gödel, George Kennan, J. Robert Oppenheimer, Erwin Panofsky, Homer A. Thompson, John von Neumann, and Hermann Weyl. This volume offers an intimate portrait in words and images of a storied institution that might best be described as a true academic village. The personal reflections collected here--written by leading figures from across the disciplines--bring this exceptional academic institution and its history vibrantly to life. The contributors to this anthology are Michael Atiyah, Chantal David, Freeman Dyson, Jane F. Fulcher, Peter Goddard, Barbara Kowalzig, Wolf Lepenies, Paul Moravec, Joan Wallach Scott, and David H. Weinberg.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aEducationvEssays. 0aEducation, Higher. 0aEducation. 0aSocial sciencesvEssays. 0aSocial sciencesvReference. 0aUniversities and collegeszUnited States. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh1 aAtiyah, Michael Francis.1 aAtiyah, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavid, Chantal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavid, Chantal.1 aDyson, Freeman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDyson, Freeman.1 aFulcher, Jane F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFulcher, Jane.1 aGoddard, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoddard, Peter.1 aKowalzig, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKowalzig, Barbara.1 aLepenies, Wolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLepenies, Wolf.1 aLevy, Serge J-F.1 aMoravec, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoravec, Paul.1 aScott, Joan Wallach, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScott, J